Installment Loan Calculator

The Installment Loan Calculator is a financial modeling tool
that provides a framework for home mortgages, auto loans,
and other types of installment loans. Given any three of the
following variables, the calculator solves for the fourth.

    PV  - principal amount
    n   - number of payments
    APR - annual interest rate
    PMT - monthly payment amount

The First Payment Date field is not used in the calculations,
but will be included in the amortization schedule to show the
date of payments.

For example, if you know the principal amount, the number of
payments, and the annual interest rate, enter 0 in the
payment amount field.

Use the up and down, tab and back-tab keys or the mouse to
navigate the fields. A chyron at the bottom of the form
lists commands which may be activated by pressing the
indicated function key or by mouse clicking the command
within the chyron.

The Form starts in overwrite mode, but can be switched to
insert mode by pressing the insert key or clicking INS in the
chyron. When in insert mode, INS will be highlighted. Press
the INS key or click INS again to toggle INS off.

After the First Payment Date is accepted, the chyron will
present the F5 Process command. The user can choose F9 Cancel
to exit the form without processing, or F5 Process to
calculate the missing variable and display the amortization
schedule.
